---
import MainLayout from '@/layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout title="About | Pattern Atlas" description="Methodology and philosophy behind this architecture handbook.">
  <section class="card">
    <h1 style="margin-top:0">About the method</h1>
    <p>
      Pattern Atlas is built as an interactive engineering handbook. It prioritizes practical reasoning over memorization,
      and explains architecture choices through context, constraints, and tradeoffs.
    </p>
    <h2>How to use this site</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Start with pattern fundamentals to build vocabulary.</li>
      <li>Move to scenarios to see how patterns combine in complete system designs.</li>
      <li>Use comparisons and quizzes to strengthen judgment.</li>
    </ol>
    <h2>Why static-first</h2>
    <p>
      The MVP is static-first for speed, reliability, and simple deployment on GitHub Pages. Interactive modules use
      client-side islands only where needed.
    </p>
    <h2>Future direction</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:0">
      The content model is designed to expand beyond junior engineers into senior tracks, manager pathways, and
      AI-agent/team-oriented architecture playbooks.
    </p>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
